cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a framework for left ventricle segmentation from cardiac cine-MRI using graph cuts and an average atlas. The use of an average atlas suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the segmentation procedure can be formulated as an energy minimization problem, which may make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of iterative graph cuts suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
